			<title>Bayreuth 2010: Of Rats and Men and Lohengrin</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://wagneroperas.libsyn.com/bayreuth-2010-of-rats-and-men-and-lohengrin]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-size: x-small;">No stranger to controversy these days <strong>The Bayreuth Festival</strong> opened at the end of July with a new production of <strong>Lohengrin</strong> directed by one of the best-known Regietheater directors, <strong>Hans Neuenfels</strong>. His tongue-in-cheek take on <strong>Richard Wagner</strong>'s most romantic opera involves setting it in a land overrun by rats. There was laughter at the Festspielhaus, there were loud boos, and there was also the beautiful singing of <strong>Jonas Kaufmann</strong> and <strong>Annette Dasch</strong> who ignited opening night with their passionate singing.</span></p>]]></description>
